main event: A UFO sighting was reported on January 16, 1967, near Charleston, South Carolina.
interesting points: The sighting was not able to be scientifically evaluated due to insufficient data,The objects were visually picked up on radar but were believed to be birds,The ground observer had difficulty clearly seeing the object,Multiple radar returns indicated the presence of several objects at high speeds,Weather conditions were reported as clear and cold during the sighting.
witness description: Ground observer and pilot, both considered reliable.
